stateDiagram-v2
  %% No double-spend — a single linear witness is spendable exactly once;
  %% two spends succeed only when two witnesses were genuinely held.
  %% Source of truth for Figure 6 in docs/theory/cost-accounting-linear-logic.md.
  %% Render: mmdc -i no-double-spend-statechart.mmd -o no-double-spend-statechart.svg

  [*] --> Has1 : single witness, delta is a
  Has1 --> Exhausted1 : consume a yields Some empty
  Exhausted1 --> Rejected1 : second consume a yields None
  Rejected1 --> [*]

  [*] --> Has2 : duplicate witness, delta is a then a
  Has2 --> Has2b : consume a yields Some of one a
  Has2b --> Empty2 : consume a yields Some empty
  Empty2 --> [*]

  note right of Rejected1
    ll_no_double_spend_single_witness:
    a lone witness is spendable exactly once.
  end note
  note right of Empty2
    ll_double_spend_requires_duplicate_witness:
    two spends succeed only with two witnesses.
  end note
